gHSu060tJ0aKHmkOn9gupg.text: Excellent sandwiches in a variety of breads to choose from. And real, genuinely friendly people behind the counter. Lovely place too.

rNyJxJq3EhK-3wltnRSrDg.text: Nice Asian fusion restaurant, inspired by Vietnamese cuisine but suited for the British palate.  Summer rolls with avocados, crayfish, or tuna, rolled in sunflower and pumpkin seeds. Not sure about the tuna. Seeds add a nice touch, especially if you have a peanut allergy.   Banh Mi sandwiches with Hanoi chicken or pork, pickled carrots and dikon, edamame pate, garlic mayo.  Friendly staff, well priced for workday bite or before hopping on the train. Will be bringing friends!

UZGwIm-xNQYXc3Q3Os1FLQ.text: Stopped by here as a tourist for a quick takeaway lunch and got a jerk chicken sandwich which seemed to have some Vietnamese flavors. The owner was very friendly and the ceiling was decorated with colorful paper cranes. It's in an arch under a street so the location was interesting as well.   This place is celebrating its 1st anniversary soon and the owner mentioned he would be celebrating it with himself and a panini... hope the best for the future of this shop!

Zau_5HmputqHFZkiTs_IQQ.text: Great little cosy shop. Great food. Be careful you don't order something spicy if you're sensitive to those types of food. The food is delivered in paper takeaway boxes . Nicely presented soup bowls too. Small outdoor and indoor dining area aswell. Great price and definitely worth it if you like Vietnamese style fusion food

YI2imK_5O6Ie4XaMgcqouQ.text: Great little shop in a cool location. We tried three sandwiches and they were all delicious and the staff was awesome -- very cool and friendly. It was our favorite meal on our trip!

Ycm2D6LVeMnfS5dTNOV6pA.text: Super friendly service! Good coffee. Made these tourists feel welcome! Thanks for all the tips!
